<div class="bios"><span style="color:#005d8f;">Rhonda Palumbo</span>,<br>
	<em>Director of Contracts and Human Resources/ Corporate Compliance Officer</em>
<p><span style="color:#005d8f;">Rhonda Palumbo</span>, 	came to Physicians Choice Dialysis with over 15 years dialysis experience. Following
		the completion of her Bachelor of Science in Business Administration at Ashland University, Rhonda worked for
		the Resolution Trust Corporation as an Assistant Technician.  In 1994 she received her Paralegal Certification
		and accepted a position as a Contracts Manager for Renal Treatment Center, Inc and Total Renal Care Group where
		she prepared and presented all of the Certificates of Need, State Licensure, Medicaid / Medicare, ESRD Network 
		licensing and approvals. In addition she was directly responsible for all legal contracts, to include the due
		diligence on all of the company's acquisitions and risk management issues. Rhonda oversaw the paralegal staff and was directly responsible
		for managing their caseload. In 1999 Rhonda was afforded the position of Assistant Facility Administrator for Delaware Valley Dialysis and
		Physicians Dialysis LLC. In this position, she was directly responsible for the expense management, inventory control, payroll, human resources,
		and risk management. In addition she was directly responsible for preparing ESRD Network reports and annual cost reports for all 
		facilities. She came to join Physicians Choice Dialysis in 2004 as our Director of Contracts and Human Resources / Corporate Compliance
		Officer where she is directly involved in every aspect of the Corporate Management daily activities. She works directly with our
		CEO and COO in the merger and acquisition of new dialysis facilities and is responsible for all regulatory matters as well
		as reviewing and revising all contracts associated with such.  In addition she is directly responsible for overseeing the management staff
		at the corporate office, and is directly involved with the corporate budget, payroll, human resources, and other matters as 
		they are presented to her.
</p></div>
